[
    {
        "text": "at seven o'clock on the morning of",
        "start": 0.96,
        "duration": 5.439
    },
    {
        "text": "monday august 21st 1911",
        "start": 3.04,
        "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
        "text": "three cleaners in the louvre museum in",
        "start": 6.399,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "paris were walking through one of the",
        "start": 8.72,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "rooms the salon carre",
        "start": 10.719,
        "duration": 5.361
    },
    {
        "text": "the three men stopped to look at one of",
        "start": 14.08,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "the world's most famous paintings",
        "start": 16.08,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "the mona lisa",
        "start": 18.4,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "this is the most valuable picture in the",
        "start": 20.88,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "world said one of the men",
        "start": 23.68,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "they say it's worth one and a half",
        "start": 26.16,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "million franks",
        "start": 28.32,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "after staring at the famous smile for a",
        "start": 30.88,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "moment or two",
        "start": 33.04,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "the three men then walked on to the",
        "start": 34.399,
        "duration": 4.721
    },
    {
        "text": "grand gallery which was the next room to",
        "start": 36.32,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "continue with some repair work",
        "start": 39.12,
        "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
        "text": "it was 8 35 a.m before they passed",
        "start": 42.16,
        "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
        "text": "through the salon carre again",
        "start": 45.28,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "and one of the men noticed that the mona",
        "start": 47.6,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "lisa had now gone",
        "start": 49.92,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "they've taken it away he laughed",
        "start": 52.96,
        "duration": 5.759
    },
    {
        "text": "they're afraid we'll steal it",
        "start": 55.76,
        "duration": 5.119
    },
    {
        "text": "the other men laughed with him and went",
        "start": 58.719,
        "duration": 4.081
    },
    {
        "text": "back to their work",
        "start": 60.879,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "it was not unusual for someone to move a",
        "start": 62.8,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "painting in the gallery",
        "start": 65.28,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "they were often taken away to be",
        "start": 67.2,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "photographed and then put back later so",
        "start": 68.88,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "the three cleaners did not think any",
        "start": 71.68,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "more about it",
        "start": 73.68,
        "duration": 5.439
    },
    {
        "text": "at 7 20 the next morning puparda one of",
        "start": 75.6,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "the louvre guards",
        "start": 79.119,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "passed through the salon carre",
        "start": 80.64,
        "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
        "text": "and noticed that the mona lisa was not",
        "start": 82.88,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "in its place",
        "start": 85.119,
        "duration": 4.161
    },
    {
        "text": "he too thought someone had taken it away",
        "start": 86.72,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "to be photographed",
        "start": 89.28,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "at nine am",
        "start": 91.84,
        "duration": 4.319
    },
    {
        "text": "a man called louis barrow arrived at the",
        "start": 93.52,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "museum",
        "start": 96.159,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "he was a painter and was painting a",
        "start": 97.6,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "picture of the salon carre",
        "start": 99.759,
        "duration": 7.121
    },
    {
        "text": "where is the mona lisa he asked pupada",
        "start": 102.96,
        "duration": 6.08
    },
    {
        "text": "it's being photographed replied the",
        "start": 106.88,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "guard",
        "start": 109.04,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "beru was annoyed",
        "start": 110.72,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "he wanted to continue his work but",
        "start": 112.64,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "decided to wait for the return of the",
        "start": 114.72,
        "duration": 3.999
    },
    {
        "text": "famous painting",
        "start": 116.88,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "he waited all morning",
        "start": 118.719,
        "duration": 5.841
    },
    {
        "text": "what are they doing with it he asked",
        "start": 121.84,
        "duration": 4.319
    },
    {
        "text": "himself",
        "start": 124.56,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "then early that afternoon",
        "start": 126.159,
        "duration": 4.561
    },
    {
        "text": "he told pupadan to go and ask the",
        "start": 128.64,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "photographer to send back the painting",
        "start": 130.72,
        "duration": 6.96
    },
    {
        "text": "i don't have much more time he said",
        "start": 134.0,
        "duration": 6.56
    },
    {
        "text": "phupardam went away and came back",
        "start": 137.68,
        "duration": 4.559
    },
    {
        "text": "quickly",
        "start": 140.56,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "the picture isn't there he said",
        "start": 142.239,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "excitedly",
        "start": 144.72,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "they don't know anything about it",
        "start": 145.92,
        "duration": 5.679
    },
    {
        "text": "and he hurried away to find his boss",
        "start": 148.8,
        "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
        "text": "georges benedict",
        "start": 151.599,
        "duration": 5.121
    },
    {
        "text": "at 3 p.m that afternoon",
        "start": 154.48,
        "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
        "text": "people were asked to leave the louvre",
        "start": 156.72,
        "duration": 5.76
    },
    {
        "text": "the museum is closing they were told but",
        "start": 159.68,
        "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
        "text": "they were not given any explanation",
        "start": 162.48,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "it was not until they read the",
        "start": 165.68,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "newspapers the next day that most of",
        "start": 167.2,
        "duration": 5.039
    },
    {
        "text": "them discovered the reason",
        "start": 169.599,
        "duration": 7.121
    },
    {
        "text": "someone had stolen the mona lisa",
        "start": 172.239,
        "duration": 7.521
    },
    {
        "text": "the museum was closed for a week",
        "start": 176.72,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "police believed that the famous painting",
        "start": 179.76,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "might still be hidden somewhere inside",
        "start": 182.0,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "and they began to search",
        "start": 184.64,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "everyone working at the museum had their",
        "start": 187.04,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "fingerprints taken",
        "start": 189.28,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "then the police found the empty frame",
        "start": 191.68,
        "duration": 5.68
    },
    {
        "text": "from the mona lisa on some back stairs",
        "start": 194.08,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "slowly they began to put together their",
        "start": 197.36,
        "duration": 5.28
    },
    {
        "text": "own picture of what had happened",
        "start": 199.92,
        "duration": 5.2
    },
    {
        "text": "the thief came to the museum on sunday",
        "start": 202.64,
        "duration": 4.879
    },
    {
        "text": "august 20th and hid in the building",
        "start": 205.12,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "after the galleries closed",
        "start": 207.519,
        "duration": 5.761
    },
    {
        "text": "at 7 30 a.m the next morning he took the",
        "start": 210.08,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "mona lisa",
        "start": 213.28,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "then went into another room and down the",
        "start": 214.72,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "stairs where the police later found the",
        "start": 217.36,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "frame",
        "start": 219.44,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "he stopped to take the painting out of",
        "start": 221.04,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "the frame",
        "start": 222.959,
        "duration": 3.441
    },
    {
        "text": "then went on to a door which led into a",
        "start": 224.0,
        "duration": 4.319
    },
    {
        "text": "courtyard",
        "start": 226.4,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "the door was locked",
        "start": 228.319,
        "duration": 4.321
    },
    {
        "text": "so he had to take off the doorknob and",
        "start": 230.159,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "break it open",
        "start": 232.64,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "he had only managed to take off the",
        "start": 234.56,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "doorknob when he heard a noise",
        "start": 236.72,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "so he pushed the doorknob into his",
        "start": 239.2,
        "duration": 4.959
    },
    {
        "text": "pocket and sat on the stairs",
        "start": 241.12,
        "duration": 6.96
    },
    {
        "text": "a man working for the museum walked by",
        "start": 244.159,
        "duration": 6.481
    },
    {
        "text": "he said later that he thought the man on",
        "start": 248.08,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "the stairs was one of the museum",
        "start": 250.64,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "cleaners and he unlocked and opened the",
        "start": 252.4,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "door for him",
        "start": 255.04,
        "duration": 4.879
    },
    {
        "text": "the thief went out into the courtyard",
        "start": 257.28,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "walked across it and opened an unlocked",
        "start": 259.919,
        "duration": 5.121
    },
    {
        "text": "door that led into the street",
        "start": 262.4,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "he ran off towards the ponte carousel",
        "start": 265.04,
        "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
        "text": "throwing the doorknob away as he ran",
        "start": 268.24,
        "duration": 6.08
    },
    {
        "text": "the police found it later",
        "start": 270.96,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "when the louvre opened again",
        "start": 274.32,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "crowds hurried to look at the empty",
        "start": 276.32,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "place on the wall of the salon carre",
        "start": 278.4,
        "duration": 6.079
    },
    {
        "text": "they could not believe their eyes",
        "start": 281.44,
        "duration": 8.0
    },
    {
        "text": "the mona lisa really had been stolen",
        "start": 284.479,
        "duration": 4.961
    },
    {
        "text": "police questioned hundreds of people",
        "start": 289.6,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "searched hundreds of houses flats and",
        "start": 292.08,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "rooms",
        "start": 294.32,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "took fingerprints",
        "start": 295.28,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "and talked to other criminals",
        "start": 296.479,
        "duration": 4.72
    },
    {
        "text": "they also found a thumb print on the",
        "start": 298.96,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "glass in the empty picture frame",
        "start": 301.199,
        "duration": 6.161
    },
    {
        "text": "but they did not find the mona lisa",
        "start": 304.32,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "and as time went on the people of france",
        "start": 307.36,
        "duration": 5.119
    },
    {
        "text": "began to believe that they would never",
        "start": 310.16,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "again see the famous picture they loved",
        "start": 312.479,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "so much",
        "start": 315.12,
        "duration": 2.639
    },
    {
        "text": "then",
        "start": 316.88,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "one morning in november in 1913",
        "start": 317.759,
        "duration": 6.401
    },
    {
        "text": "alfredo jerry a man who bought and sold",
        "start": 321.36,
        "duration": 5.36
    },
    {
        "text": "paintings opened a letter in his office",
        "start": 324.16,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "in florence in italy",
        "start": 326.72,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "the letter was from paris from someone",
        "start": 328.8,
        "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
        "text": "who signed his name as leonard",
        "start": 331.36,
        "duration": 5.76
    },
    {
        "text": "the writer said that he was an italian",
        "start": 334.8,
        "duration": 4.239
    },
    {
        "text": "living in paris",
        "start": 337.12,
        "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
        "text": "he said that he had stolen the mona lisa",
        "start": 339.039,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "and wanted to return it to italy where",
        "start": 341.68,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "it belonged and where it had been before",
        "start": 343.919,
        "duration": 4.801
    },
    {
        "text": "it was stolen during the war with france",
        "start": 346.479,
        "duration": 4.801
    },
    {
        "text": "in the 19th century",
        "start": 348.72,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "at first",
        "start": 351.28,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "jerry thought the letter was probably",
        "start": 352.4,
        "duration": 3.359
    },
    {
        "text": "from a madman",
        "start": 354.32,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "but to be sure",
        "start": 355.759,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "he showed it to his friend giovanni",
        "start": 357.12,
        "duration": 4.24
    },
    {
        "text": "poggi at the afousing gallery in",
        "start": 359.36,
        "duration": 3.679
    },
    {
        "text": "florence",
        "start": 361.36,
        "duration": 4.08
    },
    {
        "text": "they decided to write to leonard and ask",
        "start": 363.039,
        "duration": 5.921
    },
    {
        "text": "him to bring the painting to milan",
        "start": 365.44,
        "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
        "text": "on wednesday december 10th",
        "start": 368.96,
        "duration": 4.64
    },
    {
        "text": "a thin young man with a small dark",
        "start": 371.36,
        "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
        "text": "mustache arrived at jerry's office",
        "start": 373.6,
        "duration": 5.52
    },
    {
        "text": "he told jerry that the mona lisa was in",
        "start": 376.8,
        "duration": 3.76
    },
    {
        "text": "his hotel room",
        "start": 379.12,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "and that he wanted five hundred thousand",
        "start": 380.56,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "lira one hundred thousand dollars for",
        "start": 382.56,
        "duration": 4.16
    },
    {
        "text": "the picture",
        "start": 384.88,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "next day",
        "start": 386.72,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "jerry and poggi went to the young man's",
        "start": 388.08,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "room in the hotel tripoli italia",
        "start": 390.24,
        "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
        "text": "and there was the famous painting",
        "start": 393.12,
        "duration": 5.12
    },
    {
        "text": "pogie asked if he could take it to the",
        "start": 396.4,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "afuzi gallery and look at it together",
        "start": 398.24,
        "duration": 5.519
    },
    {
        "text": "with photographs of the real mona lisa",
        "start": 400.8,
        "duration": 5.04
    },
    {
        "text": "the young man agreed and the three of",
        "start": 403.759,
        "duration": 4.401
    },
    {
        "text": "them went to the gallery",
        "start": 405.84,
        "duration": 4.639
    },
    {
        "text": "later the young man went back to his",
        "start": 408.16,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "hotel and was arrested by italian",
        "start": 410.479,
        "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
        "text": "detectives",
        "start": 413.12,
        "duration": 4.479
    },
    {
        "text": "the young thief's real name was vincenzo",
        "start": 415.039,
        "duration": 5.761
    },
    {
        "text": "perugia and he was a house painter",
        "start": 417.599,
        "duration": 5.761
    },
    {
        "text": "he was actually one of the many people",
        "start": 420.8,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "questioned by the french police not long",
        "start": 423.36,
        "duration": 4.399
    },
    {
        "text": "after the painting was stolen",
        "start": 425.68,
        "duration": 4.079
    },
    {
        "text": "because he had once been employed by the",
        "start": 427.759,
        "duration": 3.681
    },
    {
        "text": "museum",
        "start": 429.759,
        "duration": 3.921
    },
    {
        "text": "they had searched his room at the time",
        "start": 431.44,
        "duration": 4.56
    },
    {
        "text": "but had found nothing",
        "start": 433.68,
        "duration": 6.0
    },
    {
        "text": "was someone hiding the painting for him",
        "start": 436.0,
        "duration": 5.84
    },
    {
        "text": "perugia had been in trouble with the law",
        "start": 439.68,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "before for a robbery",
        "start": 441.84,
        "duration": 5.52
    },
    {
        "text": "but his fingerprints kept by the police",
        "start": 444.479,
        "duration": 5.761
    },
    {
        "text": "only showed his right thumb and the",
        "start": 447.36,
        "duration": 4.88
    },
    {
        "text": "thumb print from the glass in the empty",
        "start": 450.24,
        "duration": 5.92
    },
    {
        "text": "frame had been a print of the left thumb",
        "start": 452.24,
        "duration": 4.799
    },
    {
        "text": "now",
        "start": 456.16,
        "duration": 3.36
    },
    {
        "text": "the police searched his paris rooms once",
        "start": 457.039,
        "duration": 6.081
    },
    {
        "text": "more and this time they found a 1910",
        "start": 459.52,
        "duration": 6.239
    },
    {
        "text": "diary with a list of the names of people",
        "start": 463.12,
        "duration": 5.44
    },
    {
        "text": "who bought and sold paintings in america",
        "start": 465.759,
        "duration": 5.521
    },
    {
        "text": "germany and italy",
        "start": 468.56,
        "duration": 4.96
    },
    {
        "text": "they also questioned two other italian",
        "start": 471.28,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "house painters",
        "start": 473.52,
